WILL NEVER BE COMING BACK HERE AGAIN! My family and I have been going to Pizza Den for years. And from the very beginning we could tell that the big man(I believe he is the owner) HAS come across as rude. He's made little snide comments in the past but nothing too in your face. Tonight I went by Pizza Den after a number of years and it's safe to say I will NEVER BE GOING BACK. AWFUL CUSTOMER SEVICE!!!!! I walked in and fixed my bun facing the mirror-which is 3-4 feet away from the counter which is separated from the food by glass window-when the owner told me in a VERY rude tone "Don't fix your hair here!" I was so taken aback! I couldn't even react in that moment. On the way out when I spoke to him about it he said that it was to protect the food from the air. Are you kidding me?! I was no where near the food! How can you run a business where someone can't even touch their hair in your restaurant?! You should not be running a business than! For a small family business, it is so surprising to me that they treat their customers this way. I WILL NEVER EVER EVER COME BACK HERE! Never have received such bad customer service. I have left a negative review before-but this encounter angered me so much I just had to. I will discourage anyone form ever coming here! I rather not give a business my money if they are going to treat me like that. HORRIBLE HORRIBLE HORRIBLE!!!

My kids and i used to come here every weekend  until one weeked when we were sitting down enjoying our food the old man who never speaks was in the middle of making the pizza dough when he sneezed right into the dough where tons of snot was hanging from his nose and dripped right into the dough!!!!! He then sucked it up and continued to work! (Looked like when a baby blows a big snot bubble) I was so disgusted i couldn’t finish my pizza!  Then a young guy  walked out of  the kitchen and i told him what happened. He rolled his eyes and said im so sorry! I asked, is this common for him? and with a nod and angry face he said,  we’ve spoken to him before. I said wow! Well then he shouldnt be handling the food and he again said sorry turned to him and said something to him, the old  man then goes to the kitchen comes back out with a tissue in his hand blowing his nose, throws the tissue to the garbage and without even washing his hands continues to work on the dough! Never again will I ever come here. To be fair this review is based on my experience from the summer of 2017. I don’t know if the old man is still there but this is absolutely unacceptable!

Pizza Den is conveniently located steps from the D train, making it a favorite before-stopping-home place to get their pizza on. Despite there being two other pizzerias in the immediate hood, this place always seems to be busy -- a great sign. They have all the Italian favorites and of those, their pizza is quite good. Always fresh and lots of selections. The place itself is nothing to look at really, but is clean and they have TV's usually playing sports of some kind. The folks working there all have interesting personalities, very direct but not in a rude sort of way. They keep good track of all the crazy random orders that come thru and they're always "on top of it".  They are a CASH ONLY place; no credit cards welcome here. They do delivery, but I haven't tried that service just yet.
Pizza is decent but most of the other food is frozen and not homemade. There are many better options. They are open very very late.
